      Menu

      POPULAR DISHES
      Here are some Turtle Bay faves that you might love - we've got loads more so if you like what you see, check out the menu on our website!
      Jerk Chicken
      Marinated for 24 hours in our aromatic, smoky jerk recipe, before charring on a hot grill to seal in the intense, deep flavour. Be warned – these flavours are addictive! Covered in our rich jerk gravy – with hints of thyme, allspice, scotch bonnet and more. Served with slaw and coconut rice and peas or spiced fries!
      Curry Goat
      It's a classic! One of the most iconic dishes across the islands. Tender goat marinated in aromatic spices, green seasoning, scotch bonnet, and zingy pickled veg. Served with coconut rice and peas.
      Seafood Soul Bowl
      Creamy and bursting with flavours of the ocean. Whole king prawn, squid, & salmon in a mild and creamy coconut sauce. Served with rice & peas, roasted greens and a lime wedge for an extra zing of flavour. Guaranteed to warm your soul.
      Brown Chicken Hash
      Tender chicken thighs in a rich and aromatic sauce with mashed spiced fries, topped with two crispy fried eggs & pickled veg. Our skilled chefs came up with this dish as a menu hack during their breaks, but it tasted sooo good we just had to add it to our menu!
      Coconut Prawn Rice Bowl
      Juicy prawns sauteed in a creamy coconut sauce, served with rice & peas, callaloo, sweet pineapple chow, & pickled veg - this is such a fresh dish and PERFECT for lunch. Find it in the Sunshine Bowl section of our menu.
      Chef Collin’s Mac & Cheese
      This is mac & cheese on another level - it's soooo cheesy! We add our special spice mix for flavour and top with either pulled jerk chicken, jerk mushrooms, or jerk bacon. It's pure good mood food. Find it in the Soul Food section of our menu. Guaranteed to soothe your soul...
      Trini Doubles
      Trinidad & Tobago street food. Trini Doubles are soft bara roti topped with aromatic curried chickpeas, tangy cucumber chutney, fresh coconut, and a dash of hot sauce. The deliciously addictive vegan snack is a true favourite.
      Curry Chickpea & Callaloo
      Rich and aromatic vegan curry, slowly simmered chickpea curry packed with callaloo greens and in a fragrant coconut sauce. Served with our own green seasoning, pink pickled veg and coconut rice & peas.
      Rum BBQ Wings
      Crispy, breaded chicken wings fried ‘til perfectly golden, topped with rum BBQ sauce, hot sauce and jerk mayo - these wings are IRRESISTIBLE!
      Pulled Chicken Doubles
      Hand-rolled bara roti topped with pulled chicken thigh and rum BBQ sauce with loads of fresh toppings - avo, pineapple, & pickled veg for a little zing. Find in the starters section of our menu, though this dish is perfect for sharing (you get two) or a light bite with a side of fries.
      POPULAR COCKTAILS
      Here are just some of our fave cocktails - check out the menu on our website for more cocktails. They're ALL 2-4-1 at Happy Hour (before 6.30pm & after 9pm)
      Reggae Rum Punch
      A refreshing classic. This delicious blend of Wray & Nephew, white rum, fresh lime, strawberry, pineapple & sorrel is guaranteed to transport you to an island paradise with every sip.
      Caribbean Candy Sour
      Kingston 62 Gold, amaretto & falernum, green melon liquor, apple, grapefruit & fresh lime - delicious and refreshing!
      Classic Mojito
      Your favourite classic. Appleton Signature, falernum, demerara sugar syrup, fresh mint, fresh lime, & club soda. Refreshing and light - this classic pairs perfectly with any dish!
      Summer Berry Spritz
      Project 173 Black Cherry rum, summer berry purée, fresh mint, & soda - this summer spritz is PERFECT for sunny afternoons.
      Coconut Espresso Martini
      The perfect after-dinner treat! This rich and velvety blend of dark rum & Tia Maria, coconut & cold brew coffee is guaranteed to leave you wanting more! 241 during Happy Hours!
      Passion Martini
      Our take on a porn star martini! It's our most popular cocktail for a reason! White rum & passionfruit, vanilla & orange - served with a shot of fizz. Shoot or pour - it's up to you!
      Strawberry Daiquiri
      Duppy White rum with fresh lime, berry & strawberry puree. A fruity fave!
      Watermelon Margarita
      Our take on a classic! Featuring tequila, triple sec, watermelon, sorrel, & fresh lime - this refreshing sip pairs perfectly with a spicy main. Get 2'4'1 during happy hours!
      One Love
      Dark rum & passionfruit, coconut & pineapple shaken to perfection. Our One Love will transport you to that tropical paradise with every sip. Get 2'4'1 during happy hours!
      FEATURED RUMS
      Here's just a selection of the rums we stock. Choose them on the rocks, or with any mixer. Single or double it's up to you!! Check the menu on our website for the full list of rums we serve
      Wray & Nephew Overproof
      Part of Jamaica’s culture and tradition. Strong, but with wonderfully sweet notes of molasses & banana
      Equiano Original
      Dark Rum - Naturally sweet, warm toffee and butterscotch flavours. It's totally natural with no additives including no added sugar. Equiano rum has an incredible story behind the brand - find out more on our website.
      173 Black Cherry
      Warming spices & vanilla makes this taste just like a Cherry Bakewell ! Mix with coke for classic cherry coke flavours.
      Cockspur Pineapple Rum
      Flavoured Rum - aged premium blend infused with juicy pineapple and citrus for a tropical finish with hints of coconut, it's totally delicious with lemonade (we actually think it takes like the pineapple Haribo!).
      Soggy Dollar Spiced
      One sip and this rum will transport you to the Soggy Dollar bar in the British Virgin Islands. Naturally spiced with flavour of nutmeg.
      Las Olas
      A smooth finish created using a blend of unaged pot still white rums from Barbados and Jamaica, which is then spiced in the UK using notes of vanilla, gold cherry, roasted coffee beans and more.
      POPULAR DESSERTS
      Salted Caramel Chocolate Brownie
      Rich chocolate brownie swirled with gooey caramel for the ultimate indulgent treat. With creamy coconut ice cream.
      Banana Toffee Cheesecake
      Layers of biscuit, toffee, and creamy banana, served with toffee sauce. This is indulgence on another level!

      Tripadvisor’s approach to reviews
      Before posting, each Tripadvisor review goes through an automated tracking system, which collects information, answering the following questions: how, what, where and when. If the system detects something that potentially contradicts our community guidelines, the review is not published.
      When the system detects a problem, a review may be automatically rejected, sent to the reviewer for validation, or manually reviewed by our team of content specialists, who work 24/7 to maintain the quality of the reviews on our site.
      Our team checks each review posted on the site disputed by our community as not meeting our community guidelines.
